    "summary": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Providing what is essentially the conclusion of the argument as a premise.",
        "spans": []
      }
    ],
    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "To beg the question is to assume something that you have no right to assume. What don't you have a right to assume? The conclusion itself, obviously, or any proposition that is just the conclusion stated in different words. Clearly, to use any argument in which the conclusion is also one of the premises is to reason in a circle: reasoning from the premises to the conclusion brings you back to where you started.",
