            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Example:",
            "spans": []
          },
          {
            "type": "preformatted",
            "text": "To cast abortion as a solely private moral question, ...is to lose touch with common sense: How human beings treat one another is practically the definition of a public moral matter. Of course, there are many private aspects of human relations, but the question whether one human being should be allowed fatally to harm another is not one of them. Abortion is an inescapably public matter.",
